      • getTmpFs

        @Input
@Optional
public final MapProperty<String,​String> getTmpFs()
        Docker container tmpfs support.

        The key of this map is the container target path, the value stores the tmpfs comma-separated options.

        For example, to create a temporary 50MB writeable non executable filesystem mounted under /data in the container: tmpFs = ['/data': 'rw,noexec,size=50m']

        Original documentation

        Since:
        8.0.0

      • getAutoRemove

        @Input
@Optional
public final Property<Boolean> getAutoRemove()
        Automatically remove the container when the container's process exits.

        This has no effect if restartPolicy is set.

      • getIpcMode

        @Input
@Optional
public final Property<String> getIpcMode()
        The IPC mode for the container.
        1. none - Own private IPC namespace, with /dev/shm not mounted.
        2. private - Own private IPC namespace.
        3. shareable" - Own private IPC namespace, with a possibility to share it with other containers.
        4. container <_name-or-ID_> - Join another ("shareable") containers IPC namespace.
        5. host - Use the host systems IPC namespace.

      • getSysctls

        @Input
@Optional
public final MapProperty<String,​String> getSysctls()
        The namespaced kernel parameters (sysctls) in the container.

        For example, to turn on IP forwarding in the containers network namespace: sysctls = ['net.ipv4.ip_forward':'1']

        Note:

        1. Not all sysctls are namespaced.
        2. Docker does not support changing sysctls inside of a container that also modify the host system.
